Description: Return of the Holy Family from Egypt, with Jesus walking between St Joseph and Virgin, and holding their hands; the family goes to the left, and is followed by a donkey; bridge on the right Etching
Curator's comments: Duplicate of Nn,7.23.6, see that entry for comment.
Subjects: return of the holy family from egypt
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (most likely as Crcaherode owned a group of Burdon etchings from Astley's collection)
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Sir Edward Astley (Stamped on the front with his collector's mark (L.2775))
